    `measurement_granularity` STRING COMMENT 'The time granularity at which this SLA performance measurement was captured (hourly, daily, weekly, monthly, quarterly, annual). | Column measurement_granularity (STRING) in distribution.sla_performance. Valid values are `hourly|daily|weekly|monthly|quarterly|annual`',
    `measurement_period_end` TIMESTAMP COMMENT 'The end timestamp of the measurement period for this SLA performance record. Represents the conclusion of the observation window. | Column measurement_period_end (TIMESTAMP) in distribution.sla_performance',
    `measurement_period_start` TIMESTAMP COMMENT 'The start timestamp of the measurement period for this SLA performance record. Represents the beginning of the observation window. | Column measurement_period_start (TIMESTAMP) in distribution.sla_performance',
    `measurement_source` STRING COMMENT 'The source system or monitoring tool that captured this SLA performance measurement (e.g., Akamai CDN analytics, Ericsson MediaFirst monitoring, custom QoS probe). Provides data lineage. | Column measurement_source (STRING) in distribution.sla_performance',
    `measurement_status` STRING COMMENT 'The workflow status of this SLA performance measurement record. Tracks progression from initial capture through validation, dispute resolution, and final approval. | Column measurement_status (STRING) in distribution.sla_performance. Valid values are `draft|validated|disputed|approved|closed`',
    `notes` STRING COMMENT 'Free-form notes providing additional context, operational commentary, or special circumstances related to this SLA performance measurement. | Column notes (STRING) in distribution.sla_performance',
    `partner_name` STRING COMMENT 'The name of the distribution partner (MVPD, vMVPD, OTT platform, syndication partner) to whom this SLA applies. Used for partner-specific SLA reporting and governance. | Column partner_name (STRING) in distribution.sla_performance',
    `penalty_amount` DECIMAL(18,2) COMMENT 'The monetary penalty or service credit amount assessed due to the SLA breach. Expressed in the contract currency. Null if no penalty applies. | Column penalty_amount (DECIMAL(15,2)) in distribution.sla_performance',
    `penalty_applicable_flag` BOOLEAN COMMENT 'Boolean indicator of whether a contractual penalty or service credit is applicable due to this SLA breach. True indicates financial or contractual consequences apply. | Column penalty_applicable_flag (BOOLEAN) in distribution.sla_performance',
    `penalty_currency_code` STRING COMMENT 'The three-letter ISO 4217 currency code for the penalty amount (e.g., USD, GBP, EUR). | Column penalty_currency_code (STRING) in distribution.sla_performance. Valid values are `^[A-Z]{3}$`',
    `remediation_action` STRING COMMENT 'Description of the corrective action taken to address the SLA breach or performance degradation. Documents operational response and resolution steps. | Column remediation_action (STRING) in distribution.sla_performance',
    `remediation_timestamp` TIMESTAMP COMMENT 'The timestamp when remediation action was completed and normal service levels were restored. Null if remediation is pending or not applicable. | Column remediation_timestamp (TIMESTAMP) in distribution.sla_performance',
    `root_cause_category` STRING COMMENT 'The high-level category of the root cause for SLA breach or performance degradation (e.g., network congestion, origin server failure, CDN capacity, encoding issue, third-party dependency). [ENUM-REF-CANDIDATE: network|infrastructure|capacity|configuration|third-party|content|security|unknown — promote to reference product] | Column root_cause_category (STRING) in distribution.sla_performance',
    `root_cause_description` STRING COMMENT 'Detailed textual description of the root cause analysis findings for the SLA breach or performance issue. Provides operational context for remediation and reporting. | Column root_cause_description (STRING) in distribution.sla_performance',
    `sample_size` BIGINT COMMENT 'The number of individual observations or data points used to calculate the aggregated SLA metric value. Provides statistical context for measurement confidence. | Column sample_size (BIGINT) in distribution.sla_performance',
    `source_code` STRING COMMENT 'Medallion lineage tracking column for bronze->silver->gold tracing | Column source_id (STRING) in distribution.sla_performance',
    `streaming_protocol` STRING COMMENT 'The streaming protocol used for content delivery during this measurement (HLS, MPEG-DASH, RTMP, WebRTC, Smooth Streaming). Applicable to OTT and streaming SLA measurements. | Column streaming_protocol (STRING) in distribution.sla_performance. Valid values are `HLS|MPEG-DASH|RTMP|WebRTC|Smooth Streaming`',
    `target_value` DECIMAL(18,2) COMMENT 'The target value defined in the SLA definition that the actual performance is measured against. Represents the contractual or operational commitment. | Column target_value (DECIMAL(18,4)) in distribution.sla_performance',
    `threshold_value` DECIMAL(18,2) COMMENT 'The threshold value at which an SLA breach is triggered. May differ from target value to allow for acceptable variance before breach declaration. | Column threshold_value (DECIMAL(18,4)) in distribution.sla_performance',
    `unit_of_measure` STRING COMMENT 'The unit of measure for the SLA metric values (e.g., milliseconds, percentage, Mbps, count, ratio). Provides context for interpreting actual, target, and threshold values. | Column unit_of_measure (STRING) in distribution.sla_performance',
    `updated_at` TIMESTAMP COMMENT 'Medallion lineage tracking column for bronze->silver->gold tracing | Column updated_at (TIMESTAMP) in distribution.sla_performance',
    `validated_by` STRING COMMENT 'The username or identifier of the user who validated this SLA performance measurement. Part of the approval and sign-off workflow. | Column validated_by (STRING) in distribution.sla_performance',
    `validated_timestamp` TIMESTAMP COMMENT 'The timestamp when this SLA performance measurement was validated and approved. Null if validation is pending. | Column validated_timestamp (TIMESTAMP) in distribution.sla_performance',
    `variance_percentage` DECIMAL(18,2) COMMENT 'The variance expressed as a percentage of the target value. Calculated as ((actual - target) / target) * 100. | Column variance_percentage (DECIMAL(7,4)) in distribution.sla_performance',
    `variance_value` DECIMAL(18,2) COMMENT 'The calculated variance between actual value and target value (actual minus target). Positive values indicate over-performance, negative values indicate under-performance. | Column variance_value (DECIMAL(18,4)) in distribution.sla_performance',
    CONSTRAINT pk_sla_performance PRIMARY KEY(`sla_performance_id`)
) COMMENT 'Transactional records tracking actual SLA performance measurements against defined SLA targets over time. Captures SLA definition reference, measurement period (hourly/daily/monthly), actual metric value, target value, breach flag, breach severity, affected platform/region, root-cause category, remediation action taken, and sign-off status. Distinct from sla_definition (the target) — this is the operational record of measured performance. Supports SLA reporting to distribution partners and internal governance. | Unity Catalog table: media_broadcasting_ecm.distribution.sla_performance';

