    `sla_tier` STRING COMMENT 'The contracted service level tier for this CDN configuration, determining uptime guarantees, support response times, and performance commitments. | Column sla_tier (STRING) in distribution.cdn_configuration. Valid values are `premium|standard|basic`',
    `sla_uptime_target_percent` DECIMAL(18,2) COMMENT 'The contracted uptime percentage guarantee for this CDN configuration (e.g., 99.99%). Used for SLA compliance monitoring and reporting. | Column sla_uptime_target_percent (DECIMAL(5,2)) in distribution.cdn_configuration',
    `source_code` STRING COMMENT 'Medallion lineage tracking column for bronze->silver->gold tracing | Column source_id (STRING) in distribution.cdn_configuration',
    `ssl_certificate_expiry_date` DATE COMMENT 'The expiration date of the SSL/TLS certificate. Operations teams must renew certificates before this date to prevent service disruption. | Column ssl_certificate_expiry_date (DATE) in distribution.cdn_configuration',
    `ssl_certificate_reference` STRING COMMENT 'Reference identifier or serial number of the SSL/TLS certificate deployed on the CDN property for secure HTTPS delivery. | Column ssl_certificate_reference (STRING) in distribution.cdn_configuration',
    `token_authentication_enabled` BOOLEAN COMMENT 'Indicates whether token-based authentication is enabled for this CDN configuration to prevent unauthorized access to content. | Column token_authentication_enabled (BOOLEAN) in distribution.cdn_configuration',
    `token_authentication_scheme` STRING COMMENT 'The method by which authentication tokens are passed to the CDN edge for validation (query parameter, cookie, or HTTP header). | Column token_authentication_scheme (STRING) in distribution.cdn_configuration. Valid values are `query_string|cookie|header`',
    `token_secret_key` STRING COMMENT 'The cryptographic secret key used to generate and validate authentication tokens. Must be kept confidential and rotated regularly. | Column token_secret_key (STRING) in distribution.cdn_configuration',
    `updated_at` TIMESTAMP COMMENT 'Medallion lineage tracking column for bronze->silver->gold tracing | Column updated_at (TIMESTAMP) in distribution.cdn_configuration',
    CONSTRAINT pk_cdn_configuration PRIMARY KEY(`cdn_configuration_id`)
) COMMENT 'Master configuration record for CDN (Akamai) delivery properties assigned to a delivery channel or OTT service. Captures CDN provider, property hostname, origin pull URL, caching rules (TTL, cache-control headers), token authentication settings, geo-blocking rules, failover origin configuration, SSL certificate reference, and SLA tier. Enables operations teams to manage Akamai CDN settings per channel and delivery endpoint. | Unity Catalog table: media_broadcasting_ecm.distribution.cdn_configuration';

